---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import screenshot from "../assets/runebender-xilem-screenshot.png";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Runebender"
  description="Runebender is a family of experimental font editor projects built around shared Rust core code and UFO-based type design workflows."
>
  <main id="top">
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Core / Xilem / Comfy / UFO / Very alpha</p>
        <h1 id="hero-title">Runebender</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A family of experimental font editor projects for drawing, tracing, inspecting, and
          saving UFO font sources with shared Rust code.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Project links">
          <a class="button primary" href="#family">Choose a version</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/index.html">Read the docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <figure class="screenshot-block">
        <Image
          src={screenshot}
          alt="Runebender Xilem editor screenshot showing a glyph editing workspace"
          widths={[640, 960, 1280, 1920]}
          sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 60vw"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Runebender Xilem shows the native editor path: UFO source text, bitmap reference input,
          and a glyph editing canvas. Other Runebender front-ends build on the same project line.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="status-grid" aria-label="Project status">
      <div>
        <span>01</span>
        <strong>Shared core</strong>
        <p><code>runebender-core</code> holds framework-independent editing state and data types.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>02</span>
        <strong>Multiple fronts</strong>
        <p>Xilem is the native desktop path. Comfy embeds Runebender in a ComfyUI graph.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>03</span>
        <strong>Room to grow</strong>
        <p>Druid is the older implementation; future front-ends can join the same family.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tool-strip" aria-label="Primary documentation paths">
      <a href="/docs/install.html">
        <span>RUN</span>
        <strong>Install</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/manual.html">
        <span>EDIT</span>
        <strong>Manual</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/tracing.html">
        <span>TRACE</span>
        <strong>Images</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/format.html">
        <span>UFO</span>
        <strong>Format</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/reference.html">
        <span>KEYS</span>
        <strong>Reference</strong>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/support.html">
        <span>HELP</span>
        <strong>Support</strong>
      </a>
    </section>

    <section class="section family-section" id="family" aria-labelledby="family-title">
      <div class="section-kicker">Project family</div>
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="family-title">One editor line, several front-ends.</h2>
        <p>
          Runebender is not only one app. It is a set of experiments around shared Rust editing
          code, open font sources, and different host interfaces. The names matter because each
          repository has a different role.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="family-grid">
        <article class="family-card core-card">
          <span>Foundation</span>
          <h3><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-core">Runebender Core</a></h3>
          <p>
            Platform-independent Rust types for editing state, undo, selections, entity IDs, and
            UFO-oriented data models shared by front-ends.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="family-card">
          <span>Native front-end</span>
          <h3><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-xilem">Runebender Xilem</a></h3>
          <p>
            The desktop Rust/Xilem editor path. Build from source with Cargo, open UFO sources,
            and test current glyph editing and tracing behavior.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="family-card">
          <span>ComfyUI front-end</span>
          <h3><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-comfy">Runebender Comfy</a></h3>
          <p>
            ComfyUI custom nodes and a Vue/WASM editor surface for graph-based font workflows,
            specimen rendering, workspace-backed FONT wires, and browser-hosted experiments.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="family-card">
          <span>Historical front-end</span>
          <h3><a href="https://github.com/linebender/runebender">Runebender Druid</a></h3>
          <p>
            The earlier Druid-based Runebender implementation. It anchors the project lineage but
            is not the current front-end direction.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="family-card future-card">
          <span>Future front-ends</span>
          <h3>More hosts later</h3>
          <p>
            The project is intentionally open to additional front-ends as the shared core grows and
            more interface experiments become useful.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section manual-section" id="manual" aria-labelledby="manual-title">
      <div class="section-kicker">Manual structure</div>
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="manual-title">A manual before a release page.</h2>
        <p>
          Runebender does not yet need a polished release funnel. It needs a clear map for people
          choosing between the native editor, the ComfyUI graph path, shared core code, and older
          project history.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-index">
        <article>
          <span>Start</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/install.html">Build and open a UFO</a></h3>
          <p>Start with Xilem when you want the native editor, or Comfy when you want graph-hosted tools.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Edit</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/manual.html#drawing">Draw glyphs</a></h3>
          <p>Select, pen, hyperbezier pen, knife, point type conversion, contour direction.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Trace</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/tracing.html">Bitmap to outline</a></h3>
          <p>Import a drawing, scale it to metrics, trace locally with img2bez or cloud trace.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Format</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/format.html">UFO extensions</a></h3>
          <p>Explain what data Runebender writes, including hyperbezier storage and fallbacks.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Proof</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/manual.html#preview">Preview and spacing</a></h3>
          <p>Document text preview, fitting, zoom behavior, metrics, and repeated proof strings.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Develop</span>
          <h3><a href="/docs/development.html">Architecture notes</a></h3>
          <p>Core model, Xilem UI, ComfyUI nodes, file IO, tools, and contributor paths.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split-section" id="reference" aria-labelledby="reference-title">
      <div>
        <div class="section-kicker">Technical surface</div>
        <h2 id="reference-title">Source and behavior.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="reference-stack">
        <table>
          <caption>Current repository map</caption>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Core</th>
              <td><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-core">eliheuer/runebender-core</a></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Xilem</th>
              <td><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-xilem">eliheuer/runebender-xilem</a></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Comfy</th>
              <td><a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-comfy">eliheuer/runebender-comfy</a></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Druid</th>
              <td><a href="https://github.com/linebender/runebender">linebender/runebender</a></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table>
          <caption>Shortcuts worth documenting first</caption>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>V / P / H / K</th>
              <td>Select, pen, hyperbezier pen, knife.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Space</th>
              <td>Hold for temporary preview mode.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Cmd/Ctrl + I</th>
              <td>Import background image.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Cmd/Ctrl + T</th>
              <td>Trace background image into bezier paths.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section research-section" id="research" aria-labelledby="research-title">
      <div class="section-kicker">Documentation shelves</div>
      <h2 id="research-title">Find the right page quickly.</h2>
      <div class="research-grid">
        <article>
          <h3>Topics</h3>
          <p>
            Start with the project status, alpha limits, capabilities, roadmap, glossary, and
            source map before treating any detail as stable.
          </p>
          <a href="/docs/index.html">Open docs map</a>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Tutorials</h3>
          <p>
            Follow short learning paths for first run, drawing, tracing, format inspection, and
            contributor orientation.
          </p>
          <a href="/docs/tutorials.html">Read tutorials</a>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>How-tos</h3>
          <p>
            Use task recipes for running with a file, collecting logs, tracing images, configuring
            cloud tracing, and converting hyperbeziers.
          </p>
          <a href="/docs/how-tos.html">Open recipes</a>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Reference</h3>
          <p>
            Keep shortcut lookup, format notes, source links, and troubleshooting separate from
            narrative documentation.
          </p>
          <a href="/docs/reference.html">Use shortcuts</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section manifesto" aria-labelledby="manifesto-title">
      <div class="section-kicker">Alpha warning</div>
      <h2 id="manifesto-title">Use copies. Verify against source.</h2>
      <p>
        Runebender is active experimental software. Keep real font sources under version control,
        confirm behavior against the current repository, and treat these docs as a map rather than
        a compatibility guarantee.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section resource-section" id="resources" aria-labelledby="resources-title">
      <div>
        <div class="section-kicker">Links</div>
        <h2 id="resources-title">Follow the work.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="resource-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-core">
          <strong>Runebender Core</strong>
          <span>Shared Rust editing state, undo, selections, entity IDs, and font data models.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-xilem">
          <strong>Runebender Xilem</strong>
          <span>Native Rust/Xilem editor source, screenshots, shortcuts, and current desktop workflow.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/eliheuer/runebender-comfy">
          <strong>Runebender Comfy</strong>
          <span>ComfyUI custom nodes, Vue/WASM editor surface, FONT wires, and graph workflows.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/docs/current-facts.html">
          <strong>Current facts</strong>
          <span>Compact orientation page for humans, crawlers, and coding agents.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/docs/install.html">
          <strong>Local docs</strong>
          <span>Install, manual, shortcuts, tracing, format notes, and development notes.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/linebender/runebender">
          <strong>Original Runebender</strong>
          <span>Earlier Druid implementation in the Linebender organization.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://xi.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/197075-runebender">
          <strong>Zulip</strong>
          <span>Development discussion in the Linebender chat.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://runebender.app/">
          <strong>Existing site</strong>
          <span>Historical project entry point.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
